Music will be whatever you like it to be. Make a request and it should be played. It will be the last goth night if not enough people come. So please consider ;)

I hope everyone is coming to Tabu tonight. I will be playing electro ect and if it isn't busy all hell will break loose and then there will be no other place to go except for faith and when you complain about that i will personally punch you in the face :) You get a free drink upon entry so come support the scene pls!
a bit late notice but come to Tabu tonight from 9pm onwards. Free entry and me djing. SHould be good.

1. What bill do you hate paying the most?
All bills suck. For some reason i have always felt people should pay me for everything. 

2. Where was the last place you had a romantic dinner?
Romantic dinner? I can't remember.

3. Do you regret losing your virginity to the person you lost it to?
Hell no. She was super hawt yo.

4. If you could go back and change one thing, what would it be?
I wouldn't have convinced eve to eat the apple.

5. Name of your first grade teacher?
Mrs Mc Donald.

6. What do you really want to be doing right now?
Screwing hard and fast. (sorry people)

7. What did you want to be when you were growing up?
Racecar driver.

8. How many colleges did you attend?
1.

9. Why did you choose the shirt that you have on right now?
Because it didn't smell like ass.

10. What are your thoughts on gas prices?
Evil bastards. Stop getting rich on us wasting oil and be happy with the money ethenol will make you.

11. If you could move anywhere and take someone with you, where would it be?
Outer space. I like outer space. I like it good.

12. First thought when the alarm went off this morning?
My alarm didn't go off this morning. If it did i would be concerned considering it isnt powered at this time of week.

13. Last thought before going to sleep last night?
Sleep is good. Mmmmm sleepy sleep.....

14. Do you miss being a child?
Who said i have grown up? Well i guess physically i have. In which case, no. I like my body as an adult, except for the body hair. I don't like that one bit.

Where is 15?
Up your bum.

16. What errand/chore do you despise?
Pfff. I don't do chores or errands. Please.

17. If you didn't have to work, would you volunteer?
Story of my life. And even when i work i volunteer. It is the path to righteousness. Get off the couch and help someone people!

18. Get up early or sleep in?
Both. Get up eary and enjoy the morning. Then go to bed early so you can sleep in and still wake up early the next day. 

19. What is your favorite cartoon character?
Ho mer eh er

20. Favorite thing to do at night with a girl/guy?
Umm... Screw?

21. Have you found real love yet?
Yes. And lost it. It is the way of things. To know this is very Zen.

22. When did you first start feeling old?
When i started having trouble picking up 20ish year olds.

24. Your favorite lunch meat?
Hahaha... Lunch meat. I like the word better than the actual food. But chicken. The bird of meat is mighty!

25. What do you get every time you go into Wal-Mart?
A wall. I like to buy walls. I have many of them.

26. Beach or lake?
Beach please. The beach is the edge of terra firma. You stand there looking out to sea and your nervous system feels stressed. And flopping around in the water is fun.

27. Do you think marriage is an outdated ritual?
I think it is either overpopular to the people arn't good enough to be married. If a man and women can be together for life happilly then it is ok. If not marrage is a bad thing as if they have to break up they are breaking an oath to god. As i don't believe in devorce its either marrage for life or don't get married. As i consider 99% of people do not care enough for god or are capable of being faithfull to their partner fro more than 7 years i don't think marrage should be so wide spread as it is.

28. Do you own property?
No. But i am going to at some point. Investment property is the way to make money.

29. Favorite guilty pleasure?
As if i would tell you :P

30. Favorite movie you wouldn't want anyone to find out about?
Come on. I don't want anyone to find out about it silly.
 
31. What's your drink?
Milk.

32. Cowboys or Indians?
Indians. If i get rich when im really old. im going to invent a time machine capable of transporting 100 MECH's with me back in time so i can give them to the indians. Then watch them go apeshit on the cowboys. Sorry americans. 

33. Cops or Robbers?
Cops. It would be exciting chasing and being aloud to use force.

34. Who from high school would you like to run into?
Right now one of my ex's.

35. What radio station is your car radio tuned to right now?
The ford - 106.1fm. The Colt - 106.9fm.

36. Norm or Cliff?
Your mother.

37. Grey's or The Office?
WTF?
38. Worst relationship mistake that you wish you could take back?
I don't know. WHatever.

39. Do you like the person that sits directly across from you at work?
I don't have people who sit across from me at work thank fuck. Id hate to not beable to move around for work.

40. What famous person would you like to have dinner with?
Paris hilton. Because i could offer her Special K and make an internet movie which will make me rich so i can build a time machine and 100 MECHs for the indians. 

41. Indoors or outdoors?
The outdoors indoors.

42. Have you ever crashed your vehicle?
Yes i have crashed my vehicle. And othe rpeoples too. Heaps. 

43. Have you ever had to use a fire extinguisher for its intended purpose?
Yes. A few times.

44. Last book you read?
Connan the liberator.

45. Do you have a teddy bear?
Yes i have a few. One of them is wedged in the wondow to stop the wind blowing it about. 

46. Strangest place you have ever brushed your teeth?
In my mouth. How whack is that shit?!?!

47. Somewhere in California you've never been and would like to go?
I think i went everywhere in california. But i guess i would like to go to Golds gym.

48. Do you go to church?
Yes sometimes.

49. At this point in your life, would you rather start a new career or a new relationship?
Shrugs. I'm starting a new career.  

50. How old are you?
29

There i was, standing in the foyer to Balmoral movie cinema staring up at the preview screen, half frustrated that AVP2 was not showing there. Incedently it wasn't showing at hawthorn either. This made me a sad panda. Shortly after i found myself driving around the city looking for free parking. My patience worn thin it wasn't long until i was under the Myer center with a parking ticket hanging out of my mouth and the radio shouting static at me complaining about the aparent lack of FM reception. I am reminded of Diablo the game where you are constantly decending levels until you reach hell whe i park in the Myer center. The 40 degree heat down there only adds to the ambience, the vibe... Mabo. Paris hilton decided not to be nice and hold the elevator for me. The next meat shute took me topside and a breif but inconvenient walk right around the whole bloody building ,and another elevstor ride saw me feeling poopy that the movie i wanted to see wasn't on at this place either. So i walked down to the Regent with my fingers crossed but no luck there. SO back to hell to retreive the car and paying for parking on the way out the radio buzzed back into reception life and i drive half way across town to Chermside. The "Sideh" ! It did not let me down. AVP2 was alright. Better than expected. I now find myself doing the doogy howser md thing where he makes an entry into his blog about how gheye his day was. Eat my nuggets.

I just witnessed on SBS news the spokesperson thats been campaining for several years to introduce recycled water say society can't reley on single source for water anylonger. (WHich is true) He then listed all the possibilities. Except for reverse osmosis. WHat a fucking evil controling bastard.

I need help. For awhile now i have been on my own campain to identify the solution to Australias water crisis. I have a major solution but i lack the social skills to put my points across. I have a scientificly proven technology that provides endless water. A small unit produces 25 litres of water for example. Anywhere where there is humidity in the air this technology will work. The machine literally extracts the water from the air. The ocean relenishes the water into humidity.
Its not a new technology actually. It was first invented by the ancient Greeks. It is called "Reverse osmosis". I have spent 1 year trying to spread it but something i am doing is not right. I wan't as many people to know about this before they make us drink that horrible stuff. My solution is pure and ionised as well as virtually free once set up. I think the latter is part of the reason why people in parlement dont like it.
You can build the units easy http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reverse_osmosis

There are now several thousand computers world wide working on "Folding". Every computer speeds up the process of understanding how Proteins work and efect disease and cancers, and well everything.

Stanford University is the research centre, which has distributed the Folding software. ALl information will be avaliable too all research facilities world wide.

I my self have the software running right now. And it is designed to run without bothering you. It's process priority is "LOW" So when your not at the terminal its run's at peak. But then when you use the pc is minimises itself. I infact was playing Doom 3 this morning with it running at it didn't efect gameplay at all!

This is the webpage http://folding.stanford.edu/ . I ask you to flick through it. And you can even download the software and run it your self. I fully recomend it! This will help the world!

Those running multiple computers with large uptimes should instal on each terminal.

There are teams also. If you are unsure of this don't worry. You can put in the number of my team if you like. Which is 13496. Otherwise leave it blank or 0.

Bored like a boring person.
I havent slept much, so maybe being bored can easilly turn into relaxing. Maybe even sleep. Went for a drive looking for trouble. Didnt find any despite efort. Except for a lancer gli which wassnt worht the litre of fuel spent. And a s13 K. Which also wassnt worth the efort. I remember when i had slight COmpetition against the average silvia. New tires help. Bridgestone Grid's. Have made a good contact at coleman tires. He gives me massive discounts due to work contracts. Its an intersting experiance being able to hook up from the word go. New stall converter would come in handy. And am thinking about a lower diff ratio. Maybe a 4.11/1 or more. These small changes are both cheap and have big time improvements. By a second at least. More so if i can launch around 2000rpm instead of 1000.
I Went to work for a couple of hours today. Afterwards i went ot pick up Drjon to go out ot near woodford for beltane. By using less than 5% throttle we managed 130kms on 20 litres of fuel. Mostly on high way. But marvelous fule economy. Over 6 kms/litre. Normally only get 4/litre.
*Looks over at race carburetta*
I expect to have excedingly bad fuel economy soon.
Goal of 12.00 second quarter. Soon.
Yeh may sleep now.
